@startuml fig-tcp-port-states
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center

title TCP Connect Scan — Port State Behaviour

participant "Scanner\n(connect_ex)" as scanner #FFE0B2
participant "Open Port\n(service listening)" as open #C8E6C9
participant "Closed Port\n(no service)" as closed #FFCDD2
participant "Filtered Port\n(firewall drops)" as filtered #ECEFF1

== PORT OPEN (result = 0) ==

scanner -> open : SYN
open --> scanner : SYN-ACK
scanner -> open : ACK
note right of open
connect_ex() returns 0
Three-way handshake completes
end note

== PORT CLOSED (result ≠ 0) ==

scanner -> closed : SYN
closed --> scanner : RST-ACK
note right of closed
connect_ex() returns error code
Kernel immediately rejects
end note

== PORT FILTERED (timeout) ==

scanner -> filtered : SYN
...timeout expires (0.2 s)...
note right of filtered
connect_ex() returns error code
No response received at all
The simple scanner cannot
distinguish closed from filtered
end note

legend right
A TCP connect scan uses the full
three-way handshake to test ports.
Open: handshake succeeds (result = 0).
Closed: RST received immediately.
Filtered: no response before timeout.
endlegend
@enduml
